spautor                package:spmodel                 R Documentation

_F_i_t _S_p_a_t_i_a_l _A_u_t_o_r_e_g_r_e_s_s_i_v_e _M_o_d_e_l_s

_D_e_s_c_r_i_p_t_i_o_n:

     Fit Spatial Autoregressive Models

_U_s_a_g_e:

     spautor(
       formula,
       data,
       spcov_type,
       spcov_initial,
       estmethod = "reml",
       W,
       random,
       randcov_initial,
       partition_factor,
       row_st = TRUE,
       M,
       ...
     )
     
_A_r_g_u_m_e_n_t_s:

 formula: A formula specifying the fixed effect structure

    data: A sf object or sp object with polygons

spcov_type: The covariance type: ‘"car"’ or ‘"sar"’. Not required if
          ‘spcov_initial’ is provided. In this event, ‘spcov_type’
          assumes all covariance parameters are unknown and will be
          estimated.

spcov_initial: A ‘spcov_initial’ object specifying the initial values
          for optimization and any known parameters. Not required if
          ‘spcov_type’ is provided.

estmethod: The estimation method: ‘"reml"’ or ‘"ml"’ for restricted
          maximum likelihood and maximum likelihood, respectively
          (Patterson and Thompson, 1971; Harville, 1977; Wolfinger and
          Sall, 1993)

       W: A weights matrix specifying the neighboring structure.
          Automatically calculated if omitted.

  random: A formula specifying the random effects structure

randcov_initial: A ‘randcov_initial’ object specifying the initial
          values for optimization and any known parameters. Optional.

partition_factor: A formula specifying a single partition factor.
          Different levels of the partition factor are assumed to have
          zero covariance.

  row_st: perform row standardization of ‘W’?

       M: CAR M vector required if ‘W’ is given and not symmetric - (I
          - rhoW) / M must be symmetric.

     ...: Additional arguments to ‘optim()’

_D_e_t_a_i_l_s:

     filler

_V_a_l_u_e:

     A list with many model components

_E_x_a_m_p_l_e_s:

     spmod <- spautor(y ~ x, exdata_poly, "car")
     spmod
     summary(spmod)
     

